What Does Docker actually do?

Build: Create an image with the docker file.
Ship: Move the image to different machines,Cloud VMs.
Run: Start a container from the image.

______________________________________________________________________


Process of crating a docker container.

1. Write a docker file.

  Docker file is a text file where we define:

  Base Image: an operating system, sometimes a runtime.
  Runtime: It a the software needed to run your application code.
  Dependencies: Extra libraries or packages to app needs to work.
  Copy of app code: We must move our application code into a container.
  Command to run: This tells docker what command should run when container start.

